[[File:Panorámica_de_Las_Médulas.jpg|thumb]]的[[拉斯梅德拉斯|拉斯梅德拉斯]]地區的特殊地形，這是由於羅馬帝國時期所採用的一種名為「破壞山脈」（拉丁語：ruina montium）的採礦技術而導致的。]]
羅馬帝國主要的礦產開採區有[[西班牙_(罗马行省)|西班牙]]（開採金、銀、銅、錫以及鉛礦）、[[高卢|高卢]]（金、銀、鐵礦）、[[不列顛尼亞|不列顛尼亞]]（主要開採鐵、鉛以及錫礦）、{{link-en|多瑙河地區諸行省|Danubian provinces}}（金、鐵礦）、[[马其顿行省|馬其頓]]和[[色雷斯_(羅馬行省)|色雷斯]]（金、銀礦），以及[[安納托利亞|小亞細亞]]（金、銀、鐵以及錫礦）。自[[奥古斯都|奥古斯都]]統治期間開始，羅馬帝國進行了大規模的採礦活動，並持續到了公元三世紀前期為止，因為當時的帝國逐漸衰弱，最終導致了礦業生產活動的停擺。例如羅馬帝國於大約公元271年被迫放棄了{{link-en|達契亞_(羅馬行省)|Roman Dacia|達契亞行省}}，而失去了對於當地金礦的掌握。到了公元四世紀期間，礦業活動才恢復了一定規模。<ref>"Mining," in ''Late Antiquity: A Guide to the Postclassical World'' p. 579.</ref>
[[File:World_Lead_Production.jpg|thumb]]提取出的{{link-en|冰芯|Ice core}}所估計的全球歷史鉛礦產量，其於一世紀時達到了巔峰，後來就急遽下降。<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Hong | first1 = Sungmin | author-link3 = Clair Cameron Patterson | last2 = Candelone | first2 = Jean-Pierre | last3 = Patterson | first3 = Clair C. | last4 = Boutron | first4 = Claude F. | year = 1994 | title = Greenland Ice Evidence of Hemispheric Lead Pollution Two Millennia Ago by Greek and Roman Civilizations | journal = [[Science_(journal)|Science]] | volume = 265 | issue = 5180| pages = 1841–1843 | doi=10.1126/science.265.5180.1841 | pmid=17797222| bibcode = 1994Sci...265.1841H}}</ref>一直到了18世紀中期，全球的鉛礦產量才超越了先前羅馬人所創造的數字。]]
被[[老普林尼|老普林尼]]稱作「破壞山脈」（{{lang-la|ruina montium}}）的{{link-en|水利採礦|Hydraulic mining}}技術使得羅馬人能夠以如同原始工業的規模來開採金屬。<ref>{{link-en|Wilson, Andrew|Andrew Wilson (classical archaeologist)}} (2002): "Machines, Power and the Ancient Economy", ''{{link-en|羅馬研究期刊|Society_for_the_Promotion_of_Roman_Studies#Work_of_the_society}}'', Vol. 92, pp. 1–32 (17–21, 25, 32)</ref>估計當時每年的鐵礦產量達到了82,500公噸。<ref>Craddock, Paul T. (2008): "Mining and Metallurgy", in: {{link-en|Oleson, John Peter|John Peter Oleson}} (ed.): ''The Oxford Handbook of Engineering and Technology in the Classical World'', Oxford University Press, {{ISBN|978-0-19-518731-1}}, p. 108; Sim, David; Ridge, Isabel (2002): ''Iron for the Eagles. The Iron Industry of Roman Britain'', Tempus, Stroud, Gloucestershire, {{ISBN|0-7524-1900-5}}, p. 23; Healy, John F. (1978): ''Mining and Metallurgy in the Greek and Roman World'', Thames and Hudson, London, {{ISBN|0-500-40035-0}}, p. 196. Assumes a productive capacity of c. 1.5 kg per capita. Healy, John F. (1978): ''Mining and Metallurgy in the Greek and Roman World'', Thames and Hudson, London, {{ISBN|0-500-40035-0}}, p. 196</ref>銅的年產量為15,000公噸，<ref>Hong, Sungmin; Candelone, Jean-Pierre; [[Clair_Cameron_Patterson|Patterson, Clair C.]]; Boutron, Claude F. (1996): "History of Ancient Copper Smelting Pollution During Roman and Medieval Times Recorded in Greenland Ice", ''[[Science_(journal)|Science]]'', Vol. 272, No. 5259, pp. 246–249 (366–369); cf. also Wilson, Andrew (2002): "Machines, Power and the Ancient Economy", ''{{link-en|羅馬研究期刊|Society_for_the_Promotion_of_Roman_Studies#Work_of_the_society}}'', Vol. 92, pp. 1–32 (25–29)</ref>而鉛的年產量則有80,000公噸，<ref>Hong, Sungmin; Candelone, Jean-Pierre; [[Clair_Cameron_Patterson|Patterson, Clair C.]]; Boutron, Claude F. (1994): "Greenland Ice Evidence of Hemispheric Lead Pollution Two Millennia Ago by Greek and Roman Civilizations", ''[[Science_(journal)|Science]]'', Vol. 265, No. 5180, pp. 1841–1843; Callataÿ, François de (2005): "The Graeco-Roman Economy in the Super Long-Run: Lead, Copper, and Shipwrecks", ''Journal of Roman Archaeology'', Vol. 18, pp. 361–372 (361–365); Settle, Dorothy M.; [[Clair_Cameron_Patterson|Patterson, Clair C.]] (1980): "Lead in Albacore: Guide to Lead Pollution in Americans", ''[[Science_(journal)|Science]]'', Vol. 207, No. 4436, pp. 1167–1176 (1170f.); cf. also Wilson, Andrew (2002): "Machines, Power and the Ancient Economy", ''{{link-en|羅馬研究期刊|Society_for_the_Promotion_of_Roman_Studies#Work_of_the_society}}'', Vol. 92, pp. 1–32 (25–29)</ref>後兩種礦物在當時的產量一直到了[[工業革命|工業革命]]為止都沒有被超越過。<ref>Callataÿ, François de (2005): "The Graeco-Roman Economy in the Super Long-Run: Lead, Copper, and Shipwrecks", ''Journal of Roman Archaeology'', Vol. 18, pp. 361–372 (361–369); Hong, Sungmin; Candelone, Jean-Pierre; [[Clair_Cameron_Patterson|Patterson, Clair C.]]; Boutron, Claude F. (1996): "History of Ancient Copper Smelting Pollution During Roman and Medieval Times Recorded in Greenland Ice", ''[[Science_(journal)|Science]]'', Vol. 272, No. 5259, pp. 246–249 (247, fig. 1 and 2; 248, table 1); Hong, Sungmin; Candelone, Jean-Pierre; [[Clair_Cameron_Patterson|Patterson, Clair C.]]; Boutron, Claude F. (1994): "Greenland Ice Evidence of Hemispheric Lead Pollution Two Millennia Ago by Greek and Roman Civilizations", ''[[Science_(journal)|Science]]'', Vol. 265, No. 5180, pp. 1841–1843; Settle, Dorothy M.; [[Clair_Cameron_Patterson|Patterson, Clair C.]] (1980): "Lead in Albacore: Guide to Lead Pollution in Americans", ''[[Science_(journal)|Science]]'', Vol. 207, No. 4436, pp. 1167–1176 (1170f.)</ref>而當時光西班牙地區的鉛產量就佔據了全球的四成。<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Hong | first1 = Sungmin | author-link3 = Clair Cameron Patterson | last2 = Candelone | first2 = Jean-Pierre | last3 = Patterson | first3 = Clair C. | last4 = Boutron | first4 = Claude F. | year = 1994 | title = Greenland Ice Evidence of Hemispheric Lead Pollution Two Millennia Ago by Greek and Roman Civilizations | journal = [[Science_(journal)|Science]] | volume = 265 | issue = 5180| pages = 1841–1843 | doi = 10.1126/science.265.5180.1841 | pmid=17797222 | bibcode = 1994Sci...265.1841H}}</ref>之所以會有如此高的鉛產量是因為當時的羅馬正在大規模的開採銀礦（年產量達到了200公噸），而鉛則是銀礦開採時產生的副產品。<ref>[[Clair_Cameron_Patterson|Patterson, C. C.]] (1972): "Silver Stocks and Losses in Ancient and Medieval Times", ''{{link-en|經濟史評論|The Economic History Review}}'', Vol. 25, No. 2, pp. 205–235 (228, table 6); Callataÿ, François de (2005): "The Graeco-Roman Economy in the Super Long-Run: Lead, Copper, and Shipwrecks", ''Journal of Roman Archaeology'', Vol. 18, pp. 361–372 (365f.)</ref>在公元二世紀中期左右──羅馬銀存貨量之最高峰，估計其存貨達到了10,000公噸。這個數字是[[中世紀|中世紀歐洲]]再加上公元800年左右的[[阿拔斯王朝|阿拔斯王朝]]的所有的銀重量的五至十倍。<ref>[[Clair_Cameron_Patterson|Patterson, C. C.]] (1972): "Silver Stocks and Losses in Ancient and Medieval Times", ''{{link-en|經濟史評論|The Economic History Review}}'', Vol. 25, No. 2, pp. 205–235 (216, table 2); Callataÿ, François de (2005): "The Graeco-Roman Economy in the Super Long-Run: Lead, Copper, and Shipwrecks", ''Journal of Roman Archaeology'', Vol. 18, pp. 361–372 (365f.)</ref>伴隨著大規模的金屬開採，[[格陵蘭冰原|格陵蘭冰原]]的鉛汙染程度在羅馬帝國時期達到了史前的四倍，之後又隨之降低。<ref>Hopkins, ''The Political Economy of the Roman Empire,'' p. 197.</ref>

隨著{{link-en|水利採礦|Hydraulic mining}}技術（{{link-en|沖刷找礦|Hushing}}和就地{{link-en|洗礦|Placer mining}}）的發明和遠播，以及羅馬人計畫和實行大規模採礦工程的才能，他們得以用相當於原始工業的規模開採各種金屬，不論是在各種賤金屬或貴金屬的生產量上，直至[[工業革命|工業革命]]前都極少被超越過。<ref>Wilson 2002, pp. 17–21, 25, 32</ref>當時用以[[冶煉|冶煉]]和[[鍛造|鍛造]]金屬，以及用以取暖的燃料，絕大多數是木材和[[木炭|木炭]]，而其中木炭的效果又比木材約好上了一倍。<ref>Cech 2010, p. 20</ref>此外，有些地區已經開始大量的開採煤炭。到了公元二世紀的晚期，[[不列顛尼亞|不列顛尼亞]]幾乎所有主要的煤田都已被開發利用，並開展了英格蘭和[[北海_(大西洋)|北海]]沿岸的熱絡貿易，後來貿易又延伸到了內陸的[[莱茵兰|莱茵兰]]地區，此時的當地已有使用[[烟煤|烟煤]]作為冶煉鐵礦的燃料。<ref>Smith 1997, pp. 322–324</ref>
